summaries.body: Grammy Awards: Kendrick Lamar, Taylor Swift and the Weeknd are top contenders. Mr. Lamar is up for nine awards after his hit rap album “To Pimp a Butterfly.”
Two abducted University of Rochester seniors were rescued by a SWAT unit on Sunday night, the police said. One of the students is said to have been shot in the leg.

display_asset.caption: The Asian Tiger mosquito is contributing to the spread of the dengue fever outbreak in Hawaii.

summaries.body: The number of dengue fever cases in Hawaii has risen to 136, prompting officials to warn residents and tourists to take precautions against mosquitoes that spread the virus.

display_asset.caption: This year, One Direction ruled Twitter.

summaries.body: What dominated Twitter this year? Global unrest, same-sex marriage, a boy with a clock and the breakup of One Direction topped the list.
Michelle Obama’s healthy food initiative has only led to roughly 250 new supermarkets opening in so-called food deserts since 2011, an analysis found.

summaries.body: A physician who compared Turkey’s president with a “Lord of the Rings” character is on trial. Whether he goes to jail could hinge on the answer to one question: Is Gollum evil?

display_asset.caption: Brian Shetler with the King James Bible he discovered.

summaries.body: A King James Bible first edition has been found on a library shelf at Drew University in Madison, N.J. It is a so-called “He Bible,” after an error in the Book of Ruth.
An in-office recycling machine made by Epson promises to turn waste paper into new paper in three minutes. Its price and energy consumption haven't been revealed.
Tickets for Adele's 2016 European tour sold out within minutes on Friday, prompting the singer to add several extra shows. Those tickets go on sale Monday.

Two men in central China were sentenced to at least 10 years in prison for selling Eurasian hobbies, a protected species of falcon.

summaries.body: The Secret Service is understaffed, according to a bipartisan House report that said budget-related hiring freezes had left fewer agents protecting the White House.

summaries.body: Coldplay will perform in the Super Bowl halftime show, the N.F.L. announced Thursday night during a game between Detroit and Green Bay.

Republicans in New Jersey declined to override Gov. Chris Christie’s veto of a gun-control bill that they had unanimously supported in June.
A nearly 14,000-year-old engraving on a stone found in Spain may be the earliest depiction of a campsite.
Amid large and occasionally violent protests in the streets, Ecuador's National Assembly passed a constitutional amendment to lift presidential term limits.
